Title : Run-off transcription
Text : {{technical|date=April 2014}}

A '''run-off transcription''' assay is an assay in [[molecular biology]] which is conducted ''in vitro'' to identify the position of the transcription start site (1 base pair upstream) of a specific promoter along with its accuracy and rate of ''in vitro'' [[Transcription (genetics)|transcription]].<ref name="Loewenstein">{{Cite journal
